Sea Ice Indicators Update¶

2021-1-15¶

This report presents some results of the most recent version of the algorithm for defining sea ice Freeze-up/Break-up (FUBU) dates. The NSIDC-0747 comparison plots from the previous update are included as well.

Changes since previous update:

  • require that both start and end dates be defined separately, otherwise neither are defined (see this comment)
  • end of freeze-up start search window pushed to Jan 31 of following year
  • testing of multiple higher break-up end minimum thresholds (previous was 50%, 60% and 35% are tested).
  • maps of average ice season lengths (for different minimum static break-up end thresholds)
  • consistent bin widths on histograms

Freeze-up¶

Definitions¶

Freeze-up start¶

Valid date range: 9/1 - 1/31

Threshold is set to the minimum of

  1. the sum of the mean and standard deviation of daily summer sea ice concentration (SIC), and 2) 15%.
  2. Freeze-up start is defined as the first day the daily SIC exceeds the threshold, unless mean summer SIC is > 25% (then, undefined).
  3. Undefined if freeze-up end not defined

Freeze-up end¶

Valid date range: 9/1 - 2/28

  1. Threshold is set to the maximum of 1) mean SIC in winter minus 10%, and 2) 15%.
  2. Threshold is set to the minimum of this threshold and 50%
  3. Freeze-up end is defined as the first day after the freeze-up start date where the daily SIC exceeds the threshold for the following two weeks
    a. Undefined if daily SIC is above this threshold for every day of the search period.
  4. Undefined if freeze-up start not defined

Totals maps¶

These maps present the number of days for which each of the indicators was defined for each grid cell.

NOTE: based on the new requirement that BOTH start/end need to be defined for either to be valid, these maps are the same.

NSIDC-0747 results¶

Mean lagged-date maps¶

These maps present the mean lag in days between the indicators computed from our current algorithm and the NSIDC-0747 data set, where both values are defined. I.e., the value displayed in each grid cell is calculated as "our" indicators minus "theirs", so positive values indicate that our indicator was defined before theirs on average.

Break-up¶

Definitions¶

Break-up start¶

Valid date range: 2/1 - 7/31

  1. Threshold is set to the mean winter SIC minus 2 standard deviations of the winter SIC.
  2. Break-up start is defined as the last day for which previous two weeks are above this threshold if:
    a. Mean summer SIC is less than 40%.
  3. Undefined if break-up end not defined

Break-up end¶

Valid date range: 2/1 - 9/29

  1. Threshold is set to the minimum of 1) the sum of the mean and standard deviation of daily summer SIC, and 2) 50%.
  2. Break-up end is defined as the first day where the daily SIC is less than the threshold for the following two weeks
    a. Undefined if daily SIC is less than this threshold for every day of the search period
  3. Undefined if break-up start not defined

Ice season length¶

These maps depict the mean length of the ice season in days (where defined), calculated as break-up end minus freeze-up start.

The plot on the right just has long historical ice seasons (means > 100) set to 0 to better highlight the shorter seasons found at the southern extent.
